#Text=Wikinews Interviews Australian wheelchair basketball player Caitlin de Wit
#Text=Saturday , November 30 , 2013
#Text=Thai-Japanese Bangkok Youth Center , Bangkok — Wikinews interviewed Caitlin de Wit , of the Australia women 's national wheelchair basketball team , known as the Gliders .
#Text=The Gliders are in Bangkok , Thailand , for the Asia – Oceania Zone Wheelchair Basketball Championships , which are being held at the Thai-Japanese Bangkok Youth Center .
#Text=Wikinews caught up with her on Tuesday , before the Gliders ' match against China .
#Text=Georgia Inglis at the Thai-Japanese Bangkok Youth Center , Bangkok , during the Asia-Oceania Zone Championships Image : Hawkeye7 .
#Text=( ( Wikinews ) ) Where were you born ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : In Cape Town in South Africa .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) When did you come to Australia ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : When I was six .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And then you moved to whereabouts ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : And I grew up on the Central Coast .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) A I believe you had a horse riding accident ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : I had a horse riding accident in Wagga .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What sort of horse riding were you doing ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : I was just riding with friends .
#Text=We were just like out on a ride .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And you fell off .
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And you were at uni[versity ] at the time ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah , I was at uni in Wagga and that 's where I had my accident .
#Text=And I went obviously to hospital for a little while and rehab and then I moved back to Wagga to finish my degree .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What was the degree in ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Equine studies .
#Text=Horses .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And you played sport before then ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : I ran a little bit , and I rode horses .
#Text=They were my sports .
#Text=And then in my first year of uni I started soccer .
#Text=That was my first team sport that I played .
#Text=( ( WN ) )
#Text=So what made you take up basketball ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : I suppose when I lefty hospital I was a bit bored .
#Text=I wanted something to do .
#Text=Keep me fit and occupied .
#Text=So .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) So which team did you join ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : I just joined the local Wagga team .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) There 's a local Wagga team ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah , there was .
#Text=I do n't know if its still there .
#Text=And then I joined ... and then Sarah Stewart saw me at a juniors ' camp .
#Text=And I joined what was then the Hills Hornets in the women 's league .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) So you played with the Hills Hornets .
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : mmm hmm
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And when was that ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : My first season was 2007 .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Did they win the championships that year ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) They won for a series of years straight ...
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : They won straight up until 2011 .
#Text=We had one win as the Flames .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And you joined the junior Australian women 's team ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah , the under 25s .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And where did you go with them ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : We went to Canada for the under 25 World Championships .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) When was that ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : 2011.
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And you 're still playing with the Flames in Sydney .
#Text=And you played for the Gliders at the Osaka Cup ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yep .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And that was in January this year ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah .
#Text=February maybe ? January-February ?
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And that was your first trip overseas with the senior side
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yes .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) And now this is therefore your second trip with the Gliders ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yes .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Been overseas much before then ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah .
#Text=Been overseas a little bit .
#Text=Not with basketball .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Being from South Africa .
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah .
#Text=My family traveled a little bit as a kid , so ... yeah .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Have you played anywhere overseas with any other teams ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : No.
#Text=( ( WN ) )
#Text=So how are you enjoying it here in Bangkok ?
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Good .
#Text=It 's been a really great experience .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) I keep worrying about whether they are going to blockade the airport when we need to get out of here .
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah , it should be fine .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Okay , so enjoy it !
#Text=Caitlin de Wit : Yeah !
